<L>Let him the God of Politicks appear,</L>
<L>And influence all the Arts of Peace and War.</L>
<L><PB N="21" REF="64">
Who in his Government their <HI>Birth-day</HI> had,</L>
<L>Will both be <HI>Witty, Bloody, Wi&s;e</HI> and <HI>Mad;</HI></L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Nor can Great<NOTE N="a" PLACE="foot"><HI>Charles</HI> the Ninth carre&s;s'd the Admiral <HI>Coligni,</HI> with all the To|kens and Marks of Friend&s;hip; vi&s;ited him when he had been wounded, and a&s;&s;a&s;&s;inated, wept over him, and ordered him a pretended Guard for his Security, yet at the &s;ame time had re&s;olv'd to murther him, and caus'd it to be done the next day.</NOTE> <HI>Charles the Ninth</HI> be here forgot,</L>
