<L>The Birth this <HI>Pointing Star</HI> &s;hall e're engage,</L>
<L>Shall be the be&s;t Di&s;&s;emblers of the Age;</L>
<L>Like him they'll Smile and Kill, Embrace and Hate,</L>
<L>And under fawning Ki&s;&s;es prompt your Fate.</L>
<L>May<NOTE N="b" PLACE="foot">This is a Wi&s;h only, That Providence would place &s;ome To|ken in the Face of a Hypocrite, that an innocent Man might know when he is to be wheedl'd into his De&s;truction.</NOTE> Nature Plant upon th' unhappy Brow,</L>
<L>Some Fatal Frown that Men the Wretch may know;</L>
<L>That all di&s;&s;embling Art can never hide,</L>
<L>And Innocents may guilty Snares avoid.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Ten Mighty Monarchs from the <HI>Gallick</HI> Throne,</L>
<L>For Magnitude of Crimes might &s;truggle to be &s;hown;</L>
<L>They'd all contend for Room among the Stars,</L>
<L>And jo&s;tle one another from the Spheres;</L>
<L>In equal Vilene&s;s their high Names excell,</L>
