<L><NOTE N="b" PLACE="foot">The pre&s;ent King of <HI>France,</HI> &s;uppo&s;ed attended by all the bloodie&s;t Tyrants that ever Reign'd in that Kingdom.</NOTE> See the New Growing Con&s;tellation ri&s;e,</L>
<L>And with a Train of Tyrants mount the Skies:</L>
<L>The Ance&s;tors of his Immortal Crimes,</L>
<L>Blazon'd for Heroes by the Flattering Rhimes</L>
<L>Of Antiquated Poe&s;y; but now</L>
<L>Sunk down below our Prai&s;es, and below</L>
<L>The Dignity of High Immortal Ver&s;e;</L>
<L>We Mightier Deeds, in Mightier Lines reher&s;e.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Behold the Mighty Thunderer and know,</L>
<L>The <HI>Azure-Arch</HI> can no &s;uch Heroe &s;how;</L>
<L><NOTE N="c" PLACE="foot">A Truer Thunderer than <HI>Jupiter,</HI> and much more worthy of the exalted Sphere.</NOTE> The Great, th' Invincible, are Names too &s;mall,</L>
<L>To write his Fame in Letters Capital;</L>
<L><NOTE N="d" PLACE="foot">The Titles the <HI>French</HI> Academi&s;ts and Poets frequently give their pre&s;ent Monarch in their Writings.</NOTE> A God's the only Title can explain,</L>
<L>And Suit the Mighty, the Immortal Man.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Great <HI>Jove</HI> &s;hall vail his Le&s;&s;er Maje&s;ty,</L>
<L>And to his ri&s;ing God&s;hip now give way;</L>
<L>His forked Lightning he mu&s;t now re&s;ign,</L>
