<L>With Mighty Thunders <HI>his New King</HI> Proclaim,</L>
<L>And force <HI>the Trembling Tribes</HI> to do the &s;ame?</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Becau&s;e he knew it was the <HI>Cour&s;e of things,</HI></L>
<L>And Nature's Law, that <HI>Men &s;hould Choo&s;e</HI> their Kings;</L>
<L>He knew the Early Dictate was <HI>his own,</HI></L>
<L>And Rea&s;on acted from <HI>him&s;elf</HI> alone.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>'<HI>Tis ju&s;t,</HI> &s;ays the Almighty Power, <HI>and Sen&s;e,</HI></L>
<L>For Actions are the the Words of Providence;</L>
<L><PB N="29" REF="98">
The Mouth of Con&s;equences &s;peaks aloud,</L>
<L>And Nature's Language is the Voice of God</L>
<L>'Tis ju&s;t, <HI>&s;ays he,</HI> the People &s;hould be &s;hown,</L>
<L>The Man that wears it, can de&s;erve the Crown.</L>
<L>Merit will make my Choice appear &s;o ju&s;t,</L>
<L>They'll own him fit for the intended Trust;</L>
<L>Confirm by Rea&s;on my Exalted Choice,</L>
<L>And make him King by all the Peoples Voice.</L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>Let <HI>Ammon</HI>'s Troops my Peoples Tents invade,</L>
<L>And <HI>I&s;rael</HI>'s trembling Sons, to fear betrav'd,</L>
<L>Fly from th' advancing Legions in the Fright,</L>
<L>Till <HI>Jabe&s;h</HI> Walls Embrace the <HI>Ammonite.</HI></L>
</LG>
<LG>
<L>I'll Spirit <HI>Saul,</HI> and Arm his Soul for War,</L>
<L>The <HI>Boy</HI> they &s;oorn, &s;hall in the Field appear;</L>
<L>I'll teach the unexperienc'd Youth to fight,</L>
<L>And fle&s;h him with the &s;laughter'd <HI>Ammonite:</HI></L>
<L>The General Suffrage then he'll ju&s;tly have,</L>
<L>To Rule the People, he knows how to &s;ave;</L>
<L>Their Willing Voices all the Tribes will bring,</L>
