<L>We courted Chains<NOTE N="b" PLACE="foot">'Tis to be ob&s;erv'd, That in the late Revolution &s;ome of tho&s;e Gentlemen who were the open Profe&s;&s;ors of the Doctrine of Divine Right and Ab&s;olute Subjection, were the fir&s;t that threw off the Mask, when the Practice of Royal Impo&s;ition came to bear hard upon them|&s;elves.</NOTE> but 'twas in <HI>Court-Di&s;gui&s;e,</HI></L>
<L>And <HI>Holy Fraud conceal'd</HI> the Sacred Lyes;</L>
