<LG>
<L><HI>Satyr</HI><NOTE N="a" PLACE="foot">This is an Excur&s;ion upon the Horrid Crime of Wheedling a Prince to believe &s;uch incongruous Non&s;en&s;e, as, that his Subjects, whatever they might be brought to Swear, would ever he brought to &s;ubmit to his ab&s;olute and uncontroul'd Power, that they would &s;it &s;till and &s;ee their Laws, Religion, Liberties and E&s;tates &s;ubverted, de&s;troy'd and Plunder'd, and only with Prayers and Tears invocate Heaven for Re|dre&s;s&mdash;And that they &s;hould, to delude him the more, &s;uppo$e &s;uch Ab&s;urdities of them&s;elves to him, and Swear to it al&s;o: and as all this mu&s;t be again&s;t their own Knowlege and Nature, and done on purpo&s;e to betrary him into Mi&s;chiefs they thought they &s;hould get by for the pre|&s;ent, but as they know mu&s;t ruin him at la&s;t; I think 'twas a Treachery, will be hard to be found in the World before, and therefore I &s;end the Satyr down to enquire, if there be any particular Name for &s;uch a Villany among the Devils.</NOTE> <HI>go down,</HI> and &s;earch the Pathle&s;s Deeps,</L>
