<LG>
<L>When Subjects<NOTE N="a" PLACE="foot">'Tis certain, that the Flattery of Court-Para&s;ites, and Men of De|&s;ign who too often have the Care and Favour of Princes, have led them on to the mo&s;t Tyrannick Methods of Government, by the Bait of the&s;e fooli&s;h Sugge&s;tions; thus they have prompted them to tyrannize, who would otherwi&s;e have been tolerably &s;ober, &s;welling their Thoughts with the Fancy of being God's Vicegerents, and accountable to none but him; and all, by the Hypocritical Promi&s;es of that blind Obedience on their own Parts, which they never de&s;ig'nd to pay.</NOTE> <HI>Court the Prince</HI> to tyrannize,</L>
<L><HI>And &s;well</HI> the Bladder of his Pride <HI>with Prai&s;e;</HI></L>
