<L>Th' Infernal Dialect of Treachery;</L>
<L>Learn &s;ome <HI>New Term</HI> the Modern<NOTE N="b" PLACE="foot">It was a Horrid Deceit, and cannot be enough exploded, to draw the late King into the Arbitrary Methods he fell by, only to make him ruin his Subjects, that they might &s;hare the Plunder; and afterwards abandon and overthrow him, that had hearkned only to their Advice, and I know no General Word to give it, but of the blacke&s;t Villany.</NOTE> Crime t' expre&s;s,</L>
