<L>'T had been <HI>le&s;s Crime his Sovereign</HI> to in&s;truct,</L>
<L>Than fir&s;t deceive the Prince <HI>he wou'd reject;</HI></L>
<L>In's future Conduct we &s;hou'd all confe&s;s,</L>
<L>H'had &s;hown the <HI>State&s;man</HI> more, the <HI>Villain</HI> le&s;s;</L>
<L><PB N="20" REF="145">
Rebellion would have had <HI>&s;ome fair Pretence,</HI></L>
<L>He might have reconcil'd it <HI>to his Sen&s;e;</HI></L>
