<LG>
<L><NOTE N="a" PLACE="foot">Had not the Per&s;on who this Character belongs to, &s;upported the Doctrine of ab&s;olute Obedience to the Crown, his after Conduct had been le&s;s liable to Cen&s;ure; for though, without que&s;tion, he was in the Right of it at la&s;t, yet by his own profe&s;s'd Doctrine, which he taught and encourag'd in all People, it was down-right Perj$ry and Rebellion in him, whatever it would have been in another.</NOTE> But he that had his <HI>Blinder Duty</HI> &s;wore,</L>
