<L>The&s;e the &s;ubmi&s;&s;ive Bea&s;ts Obedience fir&s;t procure:</L>
<L>If Angels, <HI>or the Devil</HI>'s in the Way,</L>
<L>Scarce <HI>Balaam</HI>'s Bea&s;t, dur&s;t in re&s;i&s;tance <HI>Bray:</HI></L>
<L>Nature oppre&s;t, groans with tyrannick Load,</L>
<L>And makes the very A&s;s <HI>refu&s;e the Road;</HI></L>
<L>Rather than bear the Cruelty of Man,</L>
<L><HI>The Bea&s;ts will &s;peak,</HI> and of the Wrong complain:</L>
<L>Nature abhors the vile &s;ubmi&s;&s;ive Slave,</L>
<L>And Sen&s;e directs Mankind <HI>to chu&s;e the Grave;</HI></L>
<L>The <HI>boiling Blood</HI> will &s;well his Rage too high,</L>
<L>And if he can't live free, <HI>he'll &s;eek to die.</HI></L>
</LG>
