<L>For &s;till<NOTE N="c" PLACE="foot">It was a great while after he had made a Conque&s;t, before he ac|cepted the Crown, and when he did, it was at the Reque&s;t, and by the Election of the People, and on Conditions, which he &s;wore to, of main|taining their Laws and Priviledges.</NOTE> the <HI>Engli&s;h</HI> Nation kept their own,</L>
